data.name: Add Operation
data.description: A JSON dictionary with inputs necessary to add a trigger
data.body:
{
    "token": ,
    "fire_date": , // Option A
    "wall_clock": , // Option B
    "local_time": , // Only relevant for wall-clock mode
    "time_zone": , // Only relevant for wall-clock mode
    "repeat_mode_indexes": , // Optional, only relevant for wall-clock mode
    "id": , // Optional
    "action":  { // See Readme
        "type": "email",
        "from": "youremail@domain.tld",
        "to": "person@domain.tld",
        "subject": "Alarm",
        "body": "This email was sent by Alarm API"
    }
}

data.name: fire_date
data.description: Either a UTC Unix timestamp int or an RSS format date

data.name: id
data.description: If provided, will replace any existing trigger with this id

data.name: local_time
data.description: RSS formatted date for the target

data.name: repeat_mode_indexes
data.description: Encoded JSON array of ints 0-6 for M-U or NULL for no repeat

data.name: time_zone
data.description: Time zone for the target

data.name: token
data.description: 64 length alphanumeric token uniquely identifying the target

data.name: wall_clock
data.description: Int referring to wall-clock time, from 0-1439 (for 12:00am to 11:59pm)

description: The Alarm API allows for the scheduling of time-based alarms which, when triggered, take some specified action.  Send email, push notifications, or call arbitrary web services, all while shortening development time, insulating your operation from the intricacies of time calculations, and expanding app capability.
